0to%20their%20country.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20he%20pointed%20out%20that%20generating%20more%20income%20for%20state%20coffers%20through%20a%20balanced%20combination%20of%20tax%20increases%C2%A0on%20the%20top%20income%20bracket%20or%20with%20a%20wealth%20tax%20was%20possible.%20%E2%80%9CBut%2C%20of%20course%2C%20this%20can%20only%20be%20done%20in%20a%20way%20that%20is%20coordinated%20internationally%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20there%20had%20been%20some%20successful%20attempts%20to%20curb%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Ftaxes%2Ft-19021286%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3Etax%20evasion%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0by%20large%20corporations%20in%202021.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOver%20130%20countries%2C%20which%20together%20account%20for%2090%25%20of%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20economic%20output%2C%20had%20also%20agreed%20on%20a%20max%2C%20and%20in%20so%20doing%20were%20trying%20to%20prevent%20companies%20from%20just%20moving%20onto%20other%20countries%20with%20better%20tax%20rates.%20Last%20year%2C%20several%20EU%20lawmakers%20proposed%20a%20similar%20global%20minimum%20tax%20on%20extremely%20high%20private%20wealth.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20Bach%20doubted%20that%20there%20would%20be%20any%20developments%20on%20this%20front%20in%20the%20near%20future%2C%20and%20this%20was%20partly%20to%20do%20with%20the%20general%20shift%20to%20the%20right%20across%20Europe.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThere%20are%20hardly%20any%20left-wing%20majorities%20left%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said%2C%20explaining%20that%20when%20it%20came%20to%20tax%20measures%2C%20it%20was%20important%20to%20have%20conservative%20and%20liberal%20parties%20on%20board%2C%20but%20these%20were%20inherently%20more%20business-friendly.%20He%20said%20that%20in%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fgermany%2Ft-17871182%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EGermany%2C%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0nothing%20would%20happen%20%E2%80%9Cin%20the%20foreseeable%20future%2C%E2%80%9D%20an