0average%20human%20lifespan%2C%20according%20to%20a%20study%20which%20found%20that%20women%20and%20individuals%20in%20developing%20nations%20are%20disproportionately%20affected.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20study%2C%20published%20recently%20in%20the%20journal%20PLOS%20Climate%2C%20evaluated%20average%20temperature%2C%20rainfall%2C%20and%20life%20expectancy%20data%20from%20191%20countries%20from%201940-2020.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%20to%20measuring%20the%20isolated%20impacts%20of%20temperature%20and%20rainfall%2C%20the%20researchers%20designed%20a%20first-of-its-kind%20composite%20climate%20change%20index%2C%20which%20combines%20the%20two%20variables%20to%20gauge%20the%20overarching%20severity%20of%20climate%20change.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EResults%20indicate%20that%20in%20isolation%2C%20a%20global%20temperature%20increase%20of%201%20degree%20Celsius%20is%20associated%20with%20an%20average%20human%20life%20expectancy%20decrease%20of%20approximately%200.44%20years%2C%20or%20about%20six%20months%20and%20one%20week.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%2010-point%20increase%20in%20the%20composite%20climate%20change%20index%20-%20which%20accounts%20for%20both%20temperature%20and%20rainfall%20-%20is%20expected%20to%20decrease%20the%20average%20life%20expectancy%20by%20six%20months%2C%20the%20researchers%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWomen%20and%20individuals%20in%20developing%20nations%20are%20disproportionately%20affected%2C%20they%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20global%20threat%20posed%20by%20climate%20change%20to%20the%20well-being%20of%20billions%20underscores%20the%20urgent%20need%20to%20address%20it%20as%20a%20public%20health%20crisis%2C%20as%20revealed%20by%20this%20study%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Amit%20Roy%20from%20Shahjalal%20University%20of%20Science%20and%20Technology%20in%20Bangladesh%20and%20The%20New%20School%20for%20Social%20Research%2C%20U.S.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20study%20emphasises%20that%20%26quot%3Bmitigation%20efforts%20to%20reduce%20greenhouse%20gas%20emissions%20and%20proactive%20initiatives%20are%20essential%20to%20safeguard%20life%20expectancy%20and%20protect%20the%20health%20of%20populations%20worldwide%2C%26quot%3B%20Roy%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETemperature%20and%20rainfall%20-%20two%20telltale%20signals%20of%20climate%20change%20-%20cause%20myriad%20public%20health%20concerns%2C%20from%20the%20acute%20and%20direct%20(e.g.%2C%20natural%20disasters%20like%20flooding%20and%20heat%20waves)%20to%20the%20indirect%20yet%20equally%20devastating%20(e.g.%2C%20respiratory%20and%20mental%20illnesses)%2C%20the%20researchers%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20impacts%20like%20these%20are%20observable%20and%20well%20documented%2C%20existing%20research%20has%20not%20established%20a%20direct%20link%20between%20climate%20change%20and%20life%20expectancy%2C%20they%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20team%20is%20hopeful%20that%20the%20composite%20climate%20change%20index%20will%20standardise%20the%20global%20conversation%20about%20climate%20change%2C%20become%20a%20usable%20metric%20for%20the%20nonscientific%20public%20and%20encourage%20collaboration%20and%20even%20friendly%20competition%20among%20countries%20to%20combat%20the%20impacts%20of%20climate%20change.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMitigating%20greenhouse%20gas%20emissions%20and%20adapting%20to%20a%20changing%20environment%20are%20of%20particular%20importance%2C%20the%20researchers%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20complement%20this%20large-scale%20approach%2C%20they%20suggest%20localised%20future%20studies%20that%20consider%20specific%20severe%20weather%20events%20(e.g.%2C%20wildfires%2C%20tsunamis%2C%20and%20floods)%2C%20the%20impacts%20of%20which%20cannot%20be%20fully%20captured%20through%20analysing%20temperature%20and%20rainfall%20alone.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3