%20of%20Education%20Report%20(ASER)%20has%20been%20recording%20trends%20in%20school%20enrolment%2C%20attendance%20and%20reading%20and%20arithmetic%20abilities%20among%20children%20aged%206-14%20years%20in%20rural%20areas%20of%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20recent%20ASER%20report%2C%20like%20the%20one%20released%20in%202017%2C%20trains%20its%20focus%20on%20older%20children%2C%20between%20the%20age%20group%20of%2014%20and%2018%2C%20covering%20four%20important%20aspects%20like%20their%20educational%20and%20career%20pathways%2C%20their%20ability%20to%20apply%20foundational%20skills%20to%20daily%20life%20situations%2C%20their%20digital%20access%20and%20skills%2C%20and%20their%20aspirations%20for%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20the%202023%20report%2C%20the%20ASER%20team%20conducted%20surveys%20in%2028%20districts%20across%2026%20states%20and%20reached%20out%20to%20over%2034%2C000%20youth%20in%20the%20age%20group%20of%2014-18%20years.%20The%20study%20finds%20that%2086.8%25%20children%20of%20the%20studied%20age%20group%20are%20enrolled%20in%20an%20educational%20institution.%20While%20there%20is%20a%20small%20gender%20gap%20noticed%2C%20the%20more%20concerning%20trend%20that%20the%20report%20identifies%20is%20the%20notable%20differences%20visible%20by%20age.%20While%20only%203.9%25%20of%2014-year-old%20youth%20were%20out%20of%20school%2C%20the%20number%20went%20up%20to%2032.6%25%20for%20the%2018%20year%20olds.%20These%20numbers%20have%2C%20however%2C%20improved%20from%20the%20time%20of%20pandemic.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20study%20found%20that%20a%20higher%20percentage%20of%20males%20(40.3%25)%20than%20females%20(28%25)%20report%20doing%20work%20other%20than%20household%20work%20for%20at%20least%2015%20days%20during%20the%20preceding%20month.%20And%20when%20it%20is%20not%20the%20household%20work%2C%20the%20youth%20are%20found%20to%20be%20engaged%20in%20family%20farm%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20study%20also%20takes%20a%20detailed%20look%20at%20the%20ability%20to%20read%20and%20comprehend%20among%20the%20surveyed%20age%20group.%20Some%20of%20the%20most%20concerning%20findings%20include%3A%20about%2025%25%20of%2014%E2%80%9318-year-olds%20still%20cannot%20read%20a%20Class%20II%20level%20text%20fluently%20in%20their%20regional%20language.%20More%20than%20half%20struggle%20with%20division%20(3-digit%20by%201-digit)%20problems%2C%20a%20skill%20that%20is%20usually%20expected%20among%20children%20of%20Class%20III%20or%20IV.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%20the%20COVID-19%20pandemic%2C%20as%20the%20world%20became%20increasingly%20reliant%20on%20technology%2C%20ASER%20set%20out%20to%20explore%20the%20current%20scenario%20of%20digital%20awareness%20and%20ability%20among%20rural%20Indian%20youth.%20The%20study%20has%20found%20that%20close%20to%2090%25%20of%20all%20youth%20have%20a%20smartphone%20in%20the%20household%20and%20know%20how%20to%20use%20it.%20Of%20those%20who%20can%20use%20a%20smartphone%2C%20males%20(43.7%25)%20are%20more%20than%20twice%20as%20likely%20to%20have%20their%20own%20smartphone%20than%20females%20(19.8%25).%20Availability%20of%20a%20computer%2Flaptop%20in%20the%20households%20is%20much%20lower%2C%20with%20only%209%25%20having%20one%20at%20home.%20Youth%20who%20have%20a%20computer%2Flaptop%20at%20home%20are%20much%20more%20likely%20to%20know%20how%20to%20use%20it%20(85%25)%20than%20those%20who%20do%20not%20(33.9%25).%20Females%20are%20less%20likely%20to%20know%20how%20to%20use%20a%20smartphone%20or%20computer%20as%20compared%20to%20males.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20study%2C%20ASER%20Centre%20director%20Wilima%20Wadhwa%20says%2C%20emphasises%20the%20importance%20of%20foundational%20learning%20and%20life%20skills%20for%20a%20reason.%20%E2%80%9CNot%20just%20for%20academic%20advancement%20but%20also%20to%20traverse%20daily%20life%2C%E2%80%9D%20Wilima%20Wadhwa%20said.%20%E2%80%9CAt%20some%20level%2C%20India%20is%20in%20a%20unique%20position%20right%20now%E2%80%A6%20For%20India%20to%20become%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20third%20largest%20economy%2C%20the%20quality%20of%20our%20labour%20force%20has%20to%20keep%20pace%20with%20our%20developmental%20needs.%20We%20can%20only%20reap%20the%20demographic%20dividend%20associated%20with%20a%20young%20population%20if%20our%20youth%20are%20well%20supported%20to%20achieve%20their%20aspirations%20and%20participate%20productively%20in%20the%20growth%20process%20of%20the%20economy.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20interview%20to%20the%20%3Cem%3EIndian%20Express%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20Dr%20Rukmini%20Banerjee%2C%20the%20CEO%20of%20Pratham%2C%20says%20that%20the%20majority%20of%20respondents%20in%20Class%2011%20or%20higher%20were%20studying%20humanities-related%20subjects%20could%20possibly%20be%20because%20that%20is%20available%20to%20the%20children%20in%20the%20village.%20%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20possible%20that%20someone%20wants%20to%20do%20science%2C%20but%20their%20local%20high%20school%20does%20not%20have%20science.%20But%20again%2C%20there%20may%20be%20other%20ways%20to%20connect%20to%20subjects%20that%20the%20local%20high%20school%20does%20not%20offer%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1705649452000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F19124917%2Fankita-konwar-zn9QqA-JTmY-unsplash.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feducation%2Fmore-that-half-14-18-year-olds-in-rural-india-cannot-do-simple-division-aser-report%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22About%2025%25%20of%2014%E2%80%9318-year-olds%20still%20cannot%20read%20a%20Class%20II%20level%20text%20fluently%20in%20their%20regional%20language.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feducation%2Fmore-that-half-14-18-year-olds-in-rural-india-cannot-do-simple-division-aser-report%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Why%20Iran%2C%20Pakistan%20Are%20At%20Loggerheads%20Despite%20A%20Common%20Enemy%3A%20Balochs%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EAn%20Iranian%20strike%20on%20Pakistan%20earlier%20this%20week%20drew%20a%20rapid%20military%20retaliation%20and%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Firan-pakistan-attack-strikes-conflict-timeline-how-iran-pakistan-conflict-has-escalated-in-past-decade-4885348%5C%22%3Eunprecedented%20escalation%20has%20raised%20fears%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20greater%20regional%20turmoil.%20The%20strikes%20come%20at%20a%20time%20when%20tensions%20have%20risen%20sharply%20across%20the%20Middle%20East.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIran%20and%20Pakistan%20share%20a%20volatile%20border%2C%20stretching%20about%20900%20kilometers%2C%20and%20have%20long%20fought%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fexplained-who-are-the-separatists-targeted-by-pakistans-strikes-in-iran-4886990%5C%22%3EBaloch%20terrorists%20in%20the%20region%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20Baloch%20people%20reside%20at%20the%20convergence%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fpakistan-attacks-iran-operation-marg-bar-sarmachar-live-updates-what-we-know-so-far-about-pakistan-marg-bar-sarmachar-in-iran-4884919%5C%22%3EPakistan%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Afghanistan%2C%20and%20Iran.%20Historically%2C%20they%20have%20demonstrated%20a%20strong%20inclination%20towards%20independence%2C%20harboring%20resentment%20for%20being%20governed%20by%20both%20Islamabad%20and%20Tehran.%20Terrorism%20has%20persisted%20in%20the%20porous%20border%20region%20for%20decades.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20the%20region's%20abundance%20of%20natural%20resources%2C%20Baloch%20separatists%20argue%20that%20their%20communities%2C%20among%20the%20most%20impoverished%20in%20the%20area%2C%20have%20reaped%20minimal%20benefits.%20Balochistan%2C%20Pakistan's%20largest%20province%20in%20terms%20of%20land%20area%2C%20has%20experienced%20a%20series%20of%20deadly%20attacks%20in%20recent%20years.%20These%20incidents%20are%20fueled%20by%20a%20long-standing%20insurgency%20led%20by%20separatists%20seeking