%E2%80%99%20or%20purely%20%E2%80%98criminal%E2%80%99%3F%20While%20one%20side%20of%20the%20coin%20says%20that%20India%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.deccanherald.com%2Fbusiness%2Feconomy%2Findia-to-be-5-trillion-economy-by-2027-28-finance-minister-2843494%23%3A~%3Atext%3DFM%2520Nirmala%2520Sitharaman%2520speaking%2520at%2C%252C%2520in%2520Gandhinagar%252C%2520on%2520Wednesday.%26amp%3Btext%3DIt%2520will%2520be%25202027%252D28%2CNirmala%2520Sitharaman%2520said%2520on%2520Wednesday.%5C%22%3Eis%20projected%20to%20become%3C%2Fa%3E%20a%20%245%20trillion%20economy%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fworld%2Findia%2Findia-be-worlds-third-largest-economy-by-2030-sp-global-ratings-2023-12-05%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DIndia-%2CIndia%2520to%2520be%2520world%2527s%2520third%252Dlargest%2Cby%25202030%2520%252DS%2526P%2520Global%2520Ratings%26amp%3Btext%3DBENGALURU%252C%2520Dec%25205%2520(Reuters)%2CRatings%2520said%2520in%2520a%2520report.%5C%22%3Ewill%20soon%20emerge%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20the%20third-largest%20economy%20in%20the%20world%2C%20the%20other%20side%20emphasises%20that%20around%2011%25%20of%20the%20population%20is%20poor%20in%20India%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.downtoearth.org.in%2Fblog%2Fgovernance%2Fjust-how-poor-is-india-10-per-cent-says-the-world-bank-85225%5C%22%3EWorld%20Bank%20data%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fblogs.lse.ac.uk%2Fsouthasia%2F2023%2F02%2F27%2Fstuffed-granaries-and-empty-stomachs-hunger-in-india%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DWith%2520enough%2520food%2520to%2520feed%2Ccrisis%252C%2520revealing%2520India%2527s%2520stern%2520inequality.%5C%22%3E189.2%20million%20people%3C%2Fa%3E%20still%20go%20to%20bed%20hungry%20every%20night.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENote%20that%20India%20has%20not%20declared%20its%20poverty%20figures%20since%202011%3B%20the%20National%20Sample%20Survey%20Office%20was%20about%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livemint.com%2Feconomy%2Fthe-simmering-debate-over-poverty-rate-11683142431495.html%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThe%2520government%2520simply%2520decided%2520not%2Cpoverty%2520relative%2520to%25202011%252D12.%5C%22%3Erelease%20a%20survey%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202017-18%2C%20but%20the%20government%20stopped%20its%20publication.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEmeritus%20Professor%20Prabhat%20Patnaik%2C%20a%20distinguished%20economist%20from%20Jawaharlal%20Nehru%20University%2C%20delves%20into%20this%20crucial%20subject%20in%20a%20conversation%20with%20Subhoranjan%20Dasgupta.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIn%20December%201984%2C%20I%20asked%20G%C3%BCnter%20Grass%2C%20arguably%20the%20greatest%20novelist%20of%20post-war%20Europe%2C%20and%20a%20trenchant%20critic%20of%20North-South%20divide%20as%20well%20as%20globalisation%3A%20What%20disturbed%20you%20most%20in%20my%20country%3F%20His%20answer%20was%2C%20%E2%80%9CA%20sea%20of%20raging%20poverty%20pockmarked%20by%20a%20few%20islands%20of%20vulgar%20luxury%20peopled%20by%20citizens%2C%20who%20are%20most%20callous%20and%20smug.%E2%80%9D%20Does%20the%20same%20picture%20prevail%20in%202024%3F%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EVery%20much%20so.%20The%20fact%20that%20the%20gap%20between%20the%20rich%20and%20the%20poor%20has%20widened%20dramatically%20will%20be%20readily%20conceded.%20Chancel%20and%20Piketty%2C%20who%20use%20income%20tax%20data%20to%20estimate%20the%20share%20of%20the%20top%201%25%20in%20national%20income%2C%20as%20a%20measure%20of%20inequality%2C%20found%20that%20this%20share%2C%20which%20had%20gone%20down%20to%206%25%20in%201982%2C%20was%2022%25%20in%202013-14%20which%20was%20higher%20than%20any%20year%20since%20the%20Income%20Tax%20Act%20was%20introduced%20in%20India%20in%201922.%20It%20was%20much%20the%20same%20in%202014-15%2C%20the%20last%20year%20for%20which%20they%20made%20an%20estimate.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENo%20matter%20what%20reservations%20one%20may%20have%20about%20their%20estimation%20method%2C%20the%20figures%20are%20too%20striking%20to%20be%20ignored.%20But%20many%20would%20claim%20that%20while%20inequality%20may%20have%20increased%2C%20poverty%20has%20come%20down%20because%20of%20our%20high%20growth%20rate%20and%20would%20cite%2C%20in%20support%20of%20their%20claim%2C%20the%20Multidimensional%20Poverty%20Index%20(MPI)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpib.gov.in%2FPressReleaseIframePage.aspx%3FPRID%3D1996271%23%3A~%3Atext%3Dlast%25209%2520years.-%2CSteep%2520decline%2520in%2520Poverty%2520Headcount%2520Ratio%2520from%252029.17%2525%2520in%25202013%2C%252D14%2520and%25202022%252D23.%5C%22%3Eprepared%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20the%20UNDP%20(United%20Nations%20Development%20Programme)%2C%20which%20shows%20a%20steep%20decline%20in%20the%20Headcount%20Poverty%20Ratio%20from%2029.17%25%20in%202013-14%20to%2011.28%25%20in%202022-23.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20MPI%2C%20however%2C%20is%20based%20on%20intellectual%20confusion.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEvery%20mode%20of%20production%20has%20the%20poor%20within%20it%20displaying%20a%20particular%20set%20of%20characteristics.%20Hence%2C%20every%20mode%20must%20have%20its%20own%20criteria%20for%20identifying%20poverty.%20Under%20feudalism%2C%20children%20in%20a%20poor%20family%20would%20be%20starved%2C%20left%20uneducated%2C%20and%20intensely%20exploited%20by%20being%20forced%20to%20join%20the%20workforce%2C%20but%20children%20in%20a%20poor%20family%20under%20capitalism%2C%20especially%20advanced%20capitalism%2C%20would%20be%20going%20to%20poor%20schools%2C%20having%20poor%20healthcare%20facilities%2C%20living%20with%20dilapidated%20furniture%20and%20run-down%20gadgets%20in%20squalid%20surroundings%2C%20and%20being%20pushed%20into%20crime.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20we%20define%20poverty%20simply%20in%20terms%20of%2C%20say%2C%20whether%20children%20go%20to%20school%20or%20not%2C%20then%20we%20would%20be%20mistaking%20the%20sheer%20introduction%20of%20capitalist%20modernity%20as%20a%20reduction%20in%20poverty%2C%20and%20needless%20to%20say%2C%20there%20would%20be%20no%20poverty%20at%20all%20so%20measured%20in%20even%20a%20middle-income%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20MPI%20is%20a%20weighted%20index%20using%20criteria%20for%20a%20household%20to%20be%20considered%20non-poor%2C%20like%20access%20to%20piped%20water%2C%20non-thatched%20dwelling%20(which%20could%20be%20merely%20a%20one%20room%20hut%20with%20a%20metal%20roof)%2C%20toilet%3B%20having%20a%20bank%20account%20(whether%20or%20not%20the%20balance%20is%20zero)%3B%20it%20gives%20only%20one-sixth%20weight%20to%20what%20is%20misleadingly%20called%20a%20nutrition%20indicator%2C%20namely%20the%20body%20mass%20index%20(BMI)%2C%20which%20does%20not%20actually%20measure%20nutritional%20status.%20Since%20it%20is%20a%20ratio%20(weight%20in%20kilograms%20divided%20by%20the%20square%20of%20height%20in%20metres)%2C%20it%20can%20have%20exactly%20the%20same%20value%20for%20persons%20of%20normal%20weight%20and%20height%2C%20as%20for%20persons%20of%20the%20same%20age%20who%20are%20seriously%20undernourished%20and%20stunted.%20Even%20the%20latter%2C%20therefore%2C%20would%20not%20be%20considered%20poor.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20society%20like%20ours%2C%20where%20different%20modes%20of%20production%20coexist%2C%20poverty%20should%20be%20defined%20in%20terms%20of%20some%20supra-mode%20index.%20Access%20to%20a%20minimum%20nutrition%20level%2C%20though%20downplayed%20by%20the%20MPI%2C%20has%20traditionally%20been%20such%20an%20internationally%20accepted%20marker.%20If%20we%20take%20access%20to%202%2C200%20calories%20per%20person%20per%20day%20in%20rural%20India%20and%202%2C100%20calories%20per%20person%20per%20day%20in%20urban%20India%2C%20as%20the%20benchmarks%20for%20defining%20poverty%20as%20the%20Planning%20Commission%20had%20done%20since%201973%2C%20then%20the%20proportion%20of%20the%20poor%20rose%20from%2058%25%20in%201993-94%20to%2068%25%20in%202011-12%20to%20over%2080%25%20in%202017-18%20in%20rural%20India.%20On%20the%20same%20dates%2C%20the%20proportions%20were%2057%25%2C%2065%25%2C%20and%20an%20estimated%2060%25%20in%20urban%20India.%20The%20increase%20in%20nutritional%20deprivation%20is%2C%20therefore%2C%20indubitable%20and%20confirms%20G%C3%BCnter%20Grass%E2%80%99s%20impression.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESome%20economists%20insist%20on%20the%20%E2%80%98determining%E2%80%99%20figures%20of%20the%20GDP%20and%20per%20capita%20income%20to%20challenge%2C%20as%20they%20say%2C%20the%20%E2%80%98inveterate%20pessimists%E2%80%99.%20How%20would%20you%20react%20to%20their%20emphasis%2C%20particularly%2C%20when%20you%20recall%20that%20not%20only%20Joseph%20Stiglitz%20and%20Amartya%20Sen%20but%20also%20Simon%20Kuznets%2C%20who%20designed%20the%20GDP%2C%20have%20focused%20on%20its%20limitation%20as%20a%20genuine%20marker%3F%20Some%20countries%2C%20like%20New%20Zealand%2C%20have%20already%20rejected%20the%20GDP%20as%20a%20dependable%20evaluator.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20find%20it%20strange%20that%20even%20people%20who%20should%20know%20better%20still%20take%20so%20much%20pride%20in%20the%20GDP%20growth%20rate.%20Apart%20from%20the%20fact%20that%20our%20growth%20rates%20are%20exaggerated%2C%20as%20a%20host%20of%20authors%20from%20Pronab%20Sen%20to%20Arvind%20Subramanian%20to%20Ashoka%20Mody%20have%20emphasised%20for%20different%20reasons%2C%20the%20GDP%20itself%20is%20conceptually%20inadequate%20for%20capturing%20well-being.%20This%20is%20not%20just%20because%20in%20the%20service%20sector%2C%20it%20is%20impossible%20to%20distinguish%20between%20a%20transfer%20and%20the%20purchase%20of%20an%20output%3B%20above%20all%2C%20it%20is%20because%20the%20distribution%20of%20output%20among%20the%20people%20is%20what%20matters.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20old%20days%20some%20oppressive%20Maharajas%20used%20%3Cem%3Ebegar%3C%2Fem%3E%20or%20corvee%20labour%20to%20build%20palaces%20for%20themselves.%20The%20construction%20of%20such%20palaces%20would%20boost%20the%20GDP%20but%20surely%20not%20be%20lauded%20as%20welfare-augmenting.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20reason%20for%20the%20current%20emphasis%20on%20GDP%20serves%20an%20official%20purpose.%20It%20can%20be%20used%20to%20legitimise%20transfers%20to%20big%20capitalists%2C%20especially%20crony%20capitalists%2C%20at%20the%20expense%20of%20the%20working%20%5Bclass%5D%20people%20on%20the%20spurious%20plea%20that%20they%20would%20make%20investments%20and%20boost%20the%20GDP%2C%20which%20is%20supposedly%20a%20good%20thing.%20Through%20the%20emphasis%20on%20the%20GDP%2C%20the%20nation%E2%80%99s%20interest%20is%20made%20identical%20with%20the%20interest%20of%20crony%20capitalists.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Findian-economy-inflation-adani-press-freedom-politics%5C%22%3EFive%20Issues%20That%20Are%20Hurting%20the%20Indian%20Economy%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWe%20agree%20that%20the%20stock%2Fshare%20market%20is%20soaring.%20But%20how%20many%20Indians%20are%20connected%20with%20the%20takeaways%20guaranteed%20by%20the%20stock%20market%3F%20What%20is%20the%20actual%20percentage%20of%20the%20beneficiaries%3F%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOnly%20about%203%25%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20population%20is%20reportedly%20connected%20with%20the%20stock%20market%20compared%20to%2055%25%20in%20the%20US.%20Even%20in%20China%2C%20the%20figure%20is%20higher%20at%2013%25.%20This%20does%20not%2C%20of%20course%2C%20mean%20that%20ordinary%20people%E2%80%99s%20money%20is%20not%20invested%20in%20the%20stock%20market%2C%20but%20it%20is%20invested%20through%20financial%20intermediaries%2C%20because%20of%20which%20people%20are%20proximately%20insulated%20from%20stock%20market%20risks.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAn%20important%20reason%20behind%20introducing%20the%20new%20pension%20scheme%20was%20to%20increase%20the%20reach%20of%20the%20stock%20market%20and%20make%20more%20people%20bear%20stock%20market%20risks.%20But%20the%20reaction%20against%20it%20shows%20people%E2%80%99s%20scepticism%20regarding%20the%20stock%20market.%20The%20people%20at%20large%2C%20therefore%2C%20have%20little%20to%20celebrate%20from%20a%20stock%20market%20boom.%20Even%20productive%20investment%20decisions%20are%20little%20influenced%20by%20the%20ongoings%20in%20the%20stock%20market%2C%20being%20largely%20determined%20by%20the%20expected%20growth%20of%20markets%20for%20goods.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIn%20FY23%2C%20banks%20in%20India%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbanking%2Fbanks-wrote-off-rs-14-56-lakh-crore-since-2014-15-govt%5C%22%3Ewaived%3C%2Fa%3E%20loans%20worth%20Rs%202.09%20lakh%20crore%2C%20of%20which%2052.3%25%20were%20loans%20from%20large%20industry%20houses.%20This%20munificence%20for%20the%20super-rich%20was%20followed%20by%20another%20drastic%20decision%20%E2%80%93%20the%20welfare%20measure%20for%20the%20poorest%20of%20the%20poor%20MGNREGA%20will%20henceforth%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flabour%2Funion-government-may-consider-case-by-case-exemptions-to-abps-mgnregs%5C%22%3Ebenefit%3C%2Fa%3E%20only%20those%20who%20have%20Aadhaar%20cards%2C%20which%20means%2C%20millions%20stand%20to%20be%20excluded.%20How%20do%20you%20explain%20this%20colossal%20dichotomy%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESuch%20dichotomy%20is%20a%20hallmark%20of%20right-wing%20governments.%20This%20government%2C%20on%20one%20pretext%20or%20another%2C%20has%20been%20trying%20to%20whittle%20down%20the%20MGNREGS.%20The%20drastic%20and%20ill-thought-out%20lockdown%20on%20account%20of%20the%20COVID-19%20pandemic%20saw%20thousands%20trekking%20back%20to%20their%20villages%3B%20they%20were%20saved%20because%20of%20MGNREGS%2C%20whose%20outlay%20had%20to%20be%20increased.%20But%20now%20immediately%20afterwards%2C%20the%20effort%20to%20truncate%20MGNREGS%20has%20started%20again.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20other%20side%2C%20loan%20waivers%20given%20to%20big%20capitalists%20by%20nationalised%20banks%20are%2C%20at%20one%20remove%2C%20just%20budgetary%20transfers.%20The%20loans%20so%20waived%20are%20partly%20just%20filched%2C%20and%20partly%20represent%20advances%20made%20under%20government%20direction%20for%20infrastructure%20investment%20that%20cannot%20be%20repaid.%20The%20colonial%20government%20had%20provided%20guaranteed%20returns%20for%20such%20investment%3B%20the%20National%20Democratic%20Alliance%20government%20likewise%20makes%20nationalised%20banks%20bear%20the%20risks%20involved.%20Its%20so-called%20economic%20%E2%80%9Cstrategy%E2%80%9D%20lies%20not%20in%20increasing%20people%E2%80%99s%20consumption%20but%20in%20inducing%20big%20capitalists%20to%20invest%20in%20infrastructure%2C%20rather%20like%20what%20the%20Russian%20economist%20Mikhail%20Tugan-Baranovsky%20had%20visualised%2C%20namely%20%E2%80%9Cinvestment%20for%20investment%E2%80%99s%20sake%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Findias-amrit-kaal-hunger-inequity-and-a-30-trillion-economy%5C%22%3EIndia%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%98Amrit%20Kaal%E2%80%99%3A%20Hunger%2C%20Inequity%20and%20a%20%2430-Trillion%20Economy%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhenever%20international%20agencies%2C%20which%20are%20not%20enemies%20of%20the%20present%20dispensation%2C%20claim%20that%20three%20out%20of%20four%20Indians%20go%20underfed%20in%20the%20country%2C%20or%20India%20is%20ranked%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fnational%2Findia-ranks-111-out-of-a-total-of-125-countries-in-global-hunger-index%2Farticle67412042.ece%23%3A~%3Atext%3DCredit%253A%2520Meeta%2520Ahlawat-%2CIndia%2520ranks%2520111%2520out%2520of%2520a%2520total%2520of%2520125%2520countries%2Ca%2520row%252C%2520citing%2520flawed%2520methodology.%5C%22%3E111%20out%20of%20125%20countries%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20Global%20Hunger%20Index%2C%20economists%20serving%20the%20government%20raise%20a%20howl%20of%20protest.%20Where%20does%20the%20truth%20lie%3F%20Are%20the%20international%20agencies%20prejudiced%20Cassandras%20or%20are%20they%20impeccably%20impartial%3F%C2%A0%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20I%20mentioned%20above%2C%20the%20increase%20in%20nutritional%20poverty%20in%20the%20neo-liberal%20era%20is%20an%20indubitable%20fact.%20The%20recent%20post-COVID-19%20distribution%20of%20free%20foodgrains%20may%20have%20moderated%20%5Bits%20impact%5D%2C%20but%20not%20nullified%20it.%20This%20again%20takes%20us%20back%20to%20what%20prevailed%20in%20the%20colonial%20period.%20The%20last%20half-century%20of%20colonial%20rule%20had%20seen%20an%20immense%20increase%20in%20nutritional%20poverty%20in%20British%20India%2C%20which%20was%20reversed%2C%20though%20not%20fully%2C%20by%20strenuous%20efforts%20of%20the%20post-independence%20governments%20prior%20to%20the%20introduction%20of%20neo-liberalism%20in%20the%20early%201990s.%20After%20the%20introduction%20of%20neo-liberalism%2C%20while%20the%20overall%20per%20capita%20availability%20of%20foodgrains%20declined%20sharply%20up%20to%202008%20and%20has%20still%20not%20climbed%20back%20to%20the%20pre-reform%20level%2C%20its%20distribution%20across%20the%20population%20has%20become%20more%20unequal%2C%20resulting%20in%20the%20calorie%20deprivation%20figures%20quoted%20earlier.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20not%20just%20the%20World%20Hunger%20Index%20that%20attests%20this.%20Even%20the%20National%20Family%20Health%20Survey%2C%20whose%20data%20are%20used%20by%20the%20MPI%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Fpmc%2Farticles%2FPMC10482272%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThe%2520prevalence%2520of%2520anaemia%2520among%2520adolescent%2520women%2520in%2520India%2520increased%2Cincrease%2520varied%2520across%2520the%2520states.%5C%22%3Eshows%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20prevalence%20of%20anaemia%20among%20women%20aged%2015-49%20rose%20from%2053%25%20in%202015-16%20to%2058%25%20in%202019-21.%20Hunger%20and%20undernutrition%20are%20stalking%20the%20country.%20India%20today%20is%20worse%20placed%20than%20both%20Sub-Saharan%20Africa%20and%20the%20%E2%80%9CLeast%20Developed