althier%20than%20you%20may%20think.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EStep%20away%20from%20the%20treadmill%20%E2%80%94%20seriously%2C%20the%20latest%20TikTok%20trend%20is%20not%20going%20to%20give%20you%20abs%2C%20grow%20your%20butt%2C%20or%20help%20you%20get%20the%20toned%20bod%20of%20your%20dreams%20no%20matter%20what%20influencers%20say%20or%20show%20you.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%26quot%3B12-3-30%26quot%3B%20workout%2C%20otherwise%20known%20as%20the%20%26quot%3Bhot%20girl%20workout%26quot%3B%20is%20the%20zombie%20exercise%20trend%20that's%20trying%20to%20suck%20the%20life%20out%20of%20your%20gym%20sessions.%20The%20so-called%20%26quot%3Bviral%26quot%3B%20routine%20seems%20to%20be%20resurrected%20every%20few%20months%20on%20various%20social%20media%20platforms%20since%20around%202019.%20The%20gist%20of%20it%20is%20that%20you%20spend%2030%20minutes%20on%20a%20treadmill%20set%20to%20three%20miles%20per%20hour%20at%20a%2012%25%20incline.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20you%20need%20to%20know%20right%20now%20is%20that%20the%2012-3-30%20trend%20is%20yet%20another%20version%20of%20the%20endless%20cardio%20machine%20trends%20with%20misleading%20promises%2C%20all%20banking%20on%20the%20myth%20that%20exercise%20is%20a%20chore%20you%20need%20to%20do%20to%20lose%20weight%20or%20look%20good.%20These%20types%20of%20workouts%20tend%20to%20target%20women%2C%20often%20playing%20on%20pressure%20to%20look%20a%20certain%20way%3A%20skinny%2C%20but%20not%20sickly%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Ffitness%2Fweight-lifting-myths-for-women%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Etoned%20without%20looking%20bulky%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20with%20a%20magazine-worthy%20thigh%20gap%20but%20inexplicably%2C%20also%20a%20dumptruck%20booty.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDon't%20get%20me%20wrong%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-five-hundred-extra-steps-per-day-live-longer-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ewalking%20is%20great%20for%20you%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20you%20should%20do%20it.%20A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbrisk-walking-slow-signs-aging-16-years-study-2022-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ebrisk%20pace%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20nice%20for%20health.%20Walking%20on%20an%20incline%20is%20fine%20for%20raising%20your%20heart%20rate%2C%20and%20can%20get%20you%20into%20a%20sweet%20spot%20of%20healthy%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-is-zone-2-cardio-exercise-training-benefits-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Elow-intensity%20cardio%20called%20Zone%202%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20if%20you%20really%2C%20truly%20love%20being%20on%20the%20treadmill%20at%20exactly%20three%20miles%20an%20hour%20at%20exactly%2012%25%20incline%20for%20exactly%2030%20minutes%2C%20and%20that%20gets%20you%20excited%20to%20go%20to%20the%20gym%2C%20follow%20your%20bliss.%20Put%20on%20your%20favorite%20podcast%20or%20playlist%2C%20and%20go%20to%20town.%20No%20judgment%20%E2%80%94%20the%20best%20exercise%20is%20the%20one%20you'll%20actually%20enjoy%20and%20keep%20doing.%20This%20just%20probably%20isn't%20it%20for%20most%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20not%20interested%20in%20arguing%20that%20this%20workout%20is%20egregiously%20bad%20(it's%20fine)%20or%20debating%20whether%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstairmaster-tips-hacks-tiktok-experts-explain-effective-2022-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eholding%20the%20handles%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20negates%20the%20benefits%20of%20the%20incline%20(an%20expert%20says%20%E2%80%A6%20meh%3F).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20just%20tired%20of%20talking%20about%20it.%20The%2012-3-30%20workout%20is%20like%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsigns-you-should-go-on-second-date-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Edate%20that%20you%20could%20mayyybe%20ask%20out%20again%3C%2Fu%3E%3