d.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.anniewright.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EAnnie%20Wright%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20licensed%20marriage%20and%20family%20therapist%20in%20Berkeley%2C%20California%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20this%20is%20called%20parentification.%20It's%20when%20a%20child%20is%20%26quot%3Bexpected%20to%20meet%20developmentally%20inappropriate%20needs%20or%20milestones%2C%26quot%3B%20Wright%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Wright%2C%20parentified%20children%20might%20be%20forced%20to%20fulfill%20logistical%20adult%20responsibilities%20like%20looking%20after%20their%20younger%20siblings%20while%20their%20parents%20are%20nowhere%20to%20be%20found.%20But%20they%20can%20also%20take%20on%20emotional%20work%20as%20well%2C%20acting%20as%20their%20parents'%20best%20friends%2C%20confidants%2C%20and%20therapists.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20Wright%20said%20there's%20no%20clinical%20research%20to%20back%20up%20which%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftypes-emotionally-immature-parents-passive-reactive-critical-absent-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Etypes%20of%20emotionally%20immature%20parents%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20parentify%20their%20children%20the%20most%2C%20she%20said%20that%20in%20her%20personal%20experience%20with%20clients%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsigns-grew-up-reactive-parent-emotionally-volatile-unstable-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ereactive%20parents%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20do%20it%20more%20often.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EReactive%20or%20emotional%20parents%20lack%20skills%20in%20emotional%20regulation%2C%20interpersonal%20communication%2C%20and%20sometimes%20even%20the%20ability%20to%20organize%20their%20lives%20to%20set%20them%20and%20their%20children%20up%20for%20success.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWright%20shared%20signs%20you%20were%20parentified%20as%20a%20child%2C%20and%20how%20it%20might%20continue%20to%20impact%20you%20as%20an%20adult.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E1.%20You%20took%20on%20way%20more%20household%20chores%20than%20your%20peers%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20it%20can%20be%20beneficial%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fkids-responsibility-chores-made-them-confident-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Echildren%20to%20have%20some%20chores%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Wright%20said%20that%20parentified%20children%20take%20on%20%26quot%3Ba%20disproportionately%20large%20amount%20of%20household%20responsibilities%26quot%3B%20such%20as%20feeling%20solely%20responsible%20for%20their%20siblings'%20or%20even%20parents'%20physical%20wellbeing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EExamples%20can%20include%20being%20expected%20to%20cook%20for%20the%20whole%20family%20at%20a%20young%20age%20or%20being%20in%20charge%20of%20always%20feeding%20and%20dressing%20your%20younger%20siblings%2C%20something%20that%20normally%20a%20parent%20would%20do.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E2.%20You%20provided%20constant%20emotional%20support%20to%20your%20parents%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWright%20said%20a%20%26quot%3Bclassic%20example%26quot%3B%20of%20someone%20parentifying%20their%20kid%20is%20%26quot%3Bexpecting%20the%20child%20to%20provide%20emotional%20support%2C%20stabilization%2C%20and%20comfort%20to%20a%20parent%20who's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsigns-symptoms-you-are-struggling-with-emotional-dysregulation-2023-9%2527%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eemotionally%20dysregulated%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20instead%20of%20the%20parents%20seeking%20that%20support%20from%20therapists%20or%20their%20friends%20or%20even%20their%20partner.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20could%20look%20like%20a%20parent%20venting%20to%20you%20about%20other%20family%20members%20or%20expecting%20you%20to%20cheer%20them%20up%20when%20they%20had%20a%20bad%20day%20at%20work%2C%20instead%20of%20giving%20you%20space%20as%20a%20child%20to%20express%20your%20own%20emotions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E3.%20You%20were%20forced%20to%20referee%20your%20parents'%20fights%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20form%20of%20parentifying%20a%20child%20is%20when%20parents%20directly%20involve%20children%20in%20their%20arguments%2C%20Wright%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20example%20she%20gave%20is%20one%20parent%20using%20a%20child%20to%20relay%20messages%20to%20the%20other%20parent%2C%20making%20their%20kid%20act%20as%20a%20referee%20in%20a%20fight%2C%20or%20using%20them%20to%20make%20the%20other%20party%20feel%20guilty.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWright%20clarified%20that%20this%20doesn't%20mean%20that%20all%20children%20who%20witnessed%20their%20parents%20fight%20were%20parentified.%20If%20you%20saw%20your%20parents%20calmly%20disagree%20about%20something%20at%20the%20dinner%20table%20and%20intervened%2C%20that's%20very%20different%20from%20your%20parents%20deliberately%20involving%20you%20in%20the%20conflict.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E4.%20You%20struggle%20with%20setting%20boundaries%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20biggest%20side%20effects%20of%20being%20parentified%20as%20a%20child%20is%20struggling%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Femotionally-immature-parent-set-boundaries-psychologist-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eset%20boundaries%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20an%20adult.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20going%20to%20impact%20every%20single%20sector%20of%20your%20life%3A%20romantic%20relationships%2C%20friendships%2C%20your%20career%2C%20and%20certainly%20your%20finances%2C%26quot%3B%20Wright%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20instance%2C%20parentified%20children%20may%20be%20less%20likely%20to%20ask%20for%20raises%2C%20push%20back%20on%20unfair%20treatment%2C%20or%20even%20pursue%20what%20they%20truly%20want%20in%20their%20lives%20because%20they're%20too%20easily%20influenced%20by%20other%20people's%20opinions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C